The paper focuses on machine learning techniques for robots to learn complex tasks and generalize to previously unseen objects and goals. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of visual observations and physical interactions, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves optimization and planning for accomplishing tasks, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
